      "id": "0dd345f3_2a7ac142",
      "file_path": "certService/src/main/java/org/onap/aaf/certservice/cmpv2client/impl/CmpResponseHelper.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 300,
      "message": "Why like this? Needs to be handled on lower level. I was expecting that from caPubs and extraCerts you will create MAP<X500Name, Certificate> and from that you will just create certificate chain, using recurrently issuerDN from certificate (signed certificate as first, further on intermediate CAs) until you will create full chain and last certificate (either self signed or one for which you can't find issuer in the map) you will put in trustedCerts.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5775,
        "name": "Pawel Baniewski",
        "display_name": "Pawel Baniewski",
        "email": "pawel.baniewski@nokia.com",
        "username": "baniewsk"
      },
